#limitation(title: [Mortality Figures: Memorial Record Selection Bias])[
The “18–21 years of lost life expectancy” figures cited above derive from memorial record studies, which capture only deaths reported to patient organisations. Population-based registry studies (Roberts et al.\ 2016, n=2,147; Smith et al.\ 2006, n=1,201) find no statistically significant elevation in all-cause mortality. The memorial record figures powerfully convey the severity of the disease but should not be cited as representative of ME/CFS mortality overall; they reflect the extreme tail of the severity distribution. See Section @subsec:all-cause-mortality for detailed methodological analysis.
]